          "Created By:"
        ],
        [
          "Sheriff: Your dedication to the law (or to the Traditions as is now the case) draws inspiration from two sources; your own desire for order and the thrill you get fom exercising your power.  Even though you dont wear a badge anymore you still have the prince backing you, so your word is still law.  Unless the prince says otherwise, of course; you dont always agree with how she interprets things.  In your opinion, these vampire rules are too liberal and the whole lot of the Kindred could be improved with some organization. Of course, you would need to be the one keeping the peace . ..",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "TS"
        ],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You're not sure how you ended up in the Brujah, not when so many of the Brujah neonates were the exact sort of low-lifes you enjoyed putting in bracelets as the mortal Sheriff of Cedar Rapids, Iowa. Maybe the fact that to succeed as a sheriff in the Midwest as a woman, you had to be no-nonsense, tough as nails and ready to throw down at the slightest provocation. You were damn good at what you did, both on the streets and playing back-room city politics. Maybe that's why your sire chose you. You quickly rose through the ranks of the Camarilla, drawing on your inherent discipline to help keep your Beast at bay. From Deputy to Scourge to Sheriff of Garden City in Kansas, Then you got a little too enthusiastic with what you thought was Anarch scum but turned out to be the favorite childe of the local Prince coming for a visit. You were quietly shuffled out of office, and it was hinted you would do better to relocate than try and survive in a city where the Prince now hated you. So you cast about for cities in need of some law and order, and finally settled on Los Angeles. If even half the rumors you hear are true, this city needs some putting back into order."
        ],
        [
          "Sire:",
          "Malcol Laskeris",
          "Reference: (If any)",
          "",
          "",
          "Clan",
          "Brujah - Stronger Beast"
        ],
        [
          "Embrace Date:",
          "1974.0",
          "Embrace Location:",
          "Garden City, KS",
          "",
          "Generation",
          "Neonate 11"
        ],
        [],
        [
          "Who You Know",
          "Your relationship to these people is described. This may mean they do not know you."
        ],
        [
          "Andy Watkins (Gangrel) (Ray Lavoie)",
          "The current Sheriff of Los Angeles, you hear he replaced the old one after the Keeper of Elysium got herself killed in an attack. He's where you'll start if you want to start climbing the political ranks again. Though you'd like his job one night, don't let on."
        ],
        [
          "Tamsin Verdin (Ventrue) (Tali Stein)",
          "A fighty Ventrue, those are rare. Most of them prefer to stick in the boardrooms, but you hear this one actually gets her hands dirty. She'd be a useful ally to cultivate."
        ],
        [
          "Archon Hale (Nosferatu) (NPC)",
          "You hear he's running the city for the Tremere Justicar. Well, he's making an absolute hash of it.That doesn't mean you can't be friends - just long enough for you to figure out how to make your mark in this city."
        ],
        [],
        [
          "Starting Goals",
          "These are recomendations, not mandates."
        ],
        [
          "Get the lay of the land. You've heard that there's some kind of war with Asian vampires going on, and some Malkavian elder either went crazy and broke the Masquerade or went crazy and went infernal. Find out what really happened, and work to hold someone responsible."
        ],
        [
          "While you want your old job back, some part of you wants to aim still higher. You've heard that there are neonate archons in this city. Maybe you can be one of them."
        ],
        [
          "Establish your reputation as a leader by organizing and executing missions against the enemy."
        ],
        [],
